cs.MM, cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.SD 

The paper deals with cross-modal retrieval between audio and video, which involves multimedia analysis and information retrieval. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also proposes a deep learning architecture for this task, which involves computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of clustering and canonical correlation analysis, which are techniques commonly used in information retrieval (cs.IR) and statistical learning (cs.SD).
